-- Divisions Seen in Heywood’s Family as Bo Trial Nears, WSJ Says
-- B y   J a n e t   O n g
-- 2013-08-19T22:55:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-19/divisions-seen-in-heywood-s-family-as-bo-trial-nears-wsj-says.html
He Zhengsheng, a Chinese lawyer who
says he represents the family of Neil Heywood, the British
businessman who was murdered, disputed a recent appeal for
compensation by Heywood’s mother, the Wall Street Journal
reported, citing an interview and a posting on Sina Weibo.
*An unidentified person close to the Heywood family confirmed
the statement from Heywood’s mother Ann, which was issued to the
WSJ earlier this month, and said the lawyer represented only
Heywood’s widow, and not his mother and sister: report
*NOTE: Bo Xilai, charged with bribery as well as abuse of power
in the death of Heywood, will face trial Aug. 22, the Xinhua
News Agency said Aug. 18.  To contact the reporter on this story:
